rename.to: TensorRT doest support opset10, onnxruntime support?

body:
yes, onnxruntime can use TensorRT backend. If TensorRT cannot support the op/opset then it will try to fall back to an onnxruntime implementation (CUDA or CPU implementation)
So in this way, onnxruntime may still be able to execute the model where TensorRT cannot by itself.
@jywu-msft Thank u so much for this clear answer..... Another thing is that does onnxruntime abundant develop or not? It seems long time not update.....

onnxruntime is in active development. there are many commits per day and our next release (0.5.0) is coming soon.

when tried to apply sample SSD object detection model.
Here is the code for object detection.

```
import numpy as np
import onnxruntime    # to inference ONNX models, we use the ONNX Runtime
import onnx
from onnx import numpy_helper
from PIL import Image

# Load the raw image
input_shape = (1, 3, 1200, 1200)
img = Image.open("blueangels.png")  
img = img.resize((1200, 1200), Image.BILINEAR)

# Preprocess and normalize the image
img_data = np.array(img)
img_data = np.transpose(img_data, [2, 0, 1])
img_data = np.expand_dims(img_data, 0)
mean_vec = np.array([0.485, 0.456, 0.406])
stddev_vec = np.array([0.229, 0.224, 0.225])
norm_img_data = np.zeros(img_data.shape).astype('float32')
for i in range(img_data.shape[1]):
    norm_img_data[:,i,:,:] = (img_data[:,i,:,:]/255 - mean_vec[i]) / stddev_vec[i]

## Run the model on the backend
session = onnxruntime.InferenceSession('ssd.onnx', None)

# get the name of the first input of the model
input_name = session.get_inputs()[0].name
bboxes, labels, scores = session.run([], {input_name: norm_img_data})
```

Here is the [ssd.onnx](https://onnxzoo.blob.core.windows.net/models/opset_10/ssd/ssd.onnx) and blueangels image is grabbed from [here](https://github.com/onnx/tutorials/blob/master/tutorials/OnnxRuntimeServerSSDModel.ipynb).

Here is the [docker](https://github.com/xonobo/onnxrt/blob/master/Dockerfile_cuda-10.0_trt) I used that builds onnxruntime and TensorRT on cuda-10.0 image.

issue.title: What's the difference between ORT with TensorRT execution provider and onnx with Tensor RT backend?

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body: Hi, I would like to know the difference between the two inference method of [onnxruntime-tensorrt](https://github.com/Azure-Samples/onnxruntime-iot-edge/blob/267362ab0306c5f97365c372adf06f9604314fef/modules/InferenceModule/main.py#L47) and [onnx-tensorrt](https://github.com/onnx/onnx-tensorrt#onnx-python-backend-usage). Could you explain a little to help to choose which method to use?
